The "classic" ketogenic diet contains a 4:1 ratio by weight of fat to combined protein and carbohydrate.
Most children improved in both seizure control and alertness: results that were similar to the classic ketogenic diet.
In a five-year trial starting in 2001, Elizabeth Neil at the Great Ormond Street Hospital, compared children on the classical diet with children on an MCT variant that derived 45% of the calories from MCT oil.
